  <description>Perennials, (20–)30–60(–80) cm. Stems 1–3+ (ridged), erect, branched (usually glabrous proximally, puberulent distally). Leaves mainly cauline; petiolate; blades ovate to rounded-deltate, 4–10+ × 1.5–4 cm, usually 1–2-pinnately lobed (primary lobes 3–5+ pairs, ± ovate), ultimate margins pinnatifid to dentate, faces (at least abaxial) usually puberulent, gland-dotted. Heads 5–20(–30) in corymbiform arrays. Involucres 5–7 mm diam. Ray florets 10–21+ (more in “doubles”), pistillate, fertile; corollas white, laminae 2–8(–12) mm. Disc corollas ca. 2 mm. Cypselae ± columnar, 1–2 mm, 5–10-ribbed; pappi 0 or coroniform, 0.1–0.2+ mm. 2n = 18.</description>
